like_page: PageJuly 22 · I think Trump's speech is kind of brilliant, in a scary and disturbing way. He is the first serious national candidate in our or any other major democracy to sp...ell out the battle lines that people on a grassroots level have woken up to -- the battle is between what is left of nation-states that are democracies, in which people have some say over their national policies and can pay attention to national values and priorities -- versus the global collective script of what is emerging clearly as an internationally globalized set agenda, passed in bills such as TPP, above the heads of nation-states, Congresses and Parliaments. This fear about actually what is actually bad and scary about globalization and citizen decision-making is what led to British voters choosing Brexit. I am not taking sides in any of these discussions but noting that you don't have to be an idiot or a racist to see the value of a nation-state with its own citizens' local or national agenda, against the agendas of globalized special interests who increasingly want to transcend parliaments and congresses.  Trump is not wrong to spell out this critique -- it is the center of history right now in the West -- and I for one am worried about the loss of the nation-state - - about what is now obvious as being the clearly planned erosion of the powers of democracies in nation-states, in the face of a globalization agenda by special interests.  Much more disturbing to me than this legitimate critique, is his hyping of the terror threat -- and his manipulation of some terrible recent news events to use fear to boost his mandate. America is far more safe and stable than the 24 hour news cycle proposes; and crime is tragic, but it should not be used to hijack listeners' neocortical responses. As far as his even mentioning the poor, well that is a welcome addition to political discussion -- democrats would do well to match that concern as very few people left in the US any longer feel even middle class. A skillful if in some ways troubling performance.
